<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{6}{y}=-{46}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}-{2}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{5}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+-{6}{y}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{46}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{46}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{\left(\frac{{-{46}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{8}}}}\right)}+-{2}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{8}}{{-{{8}}}}\cdot{\left(-{46}\right)}--\frac{{8}}{{-{{8}}}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{46}-{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{2}{y}=-{26}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}=-{26}--{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({6}+{\left(-{2}\right)}\right)}{y}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{4}{y}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{20}}{{4}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={5}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+-{6}{\left({5}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}+{\left(-{30}\right)}=-{46}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{46}-{\left(-{30}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{8}{x}=-{16}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{16}}{{-{{8}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{5}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

